24 void ArmUs::Run()
25 {
26  ros::Rate loop_rate(ROS_RATE);
27 
28  while (ros::ok())
29  {
30  // Calculate motor velocities depending if in joint or cartesian mode
31  m_arm_us_info->calculate_motor_velocities();
32 
33  if (!ros::ok())
34  {
35  // Set all motor velocities to 0
36  send_cmd_motor_stop();
37  }
38  else
39  {
40  // Send motor velocities to interface that checks joint limits and returns joint angles
41  send_cmd_motor();
42  }
43 
44  // Send info to GUI : Motor velocities, positions, etc
45  send_gui_info();
46  // Send info to graph for real time representation of arm in Rviz : Joint angles
47  send_3d_graph_info();
48 
49  // Check callbacks
50  ros::spinOnce();
51  loop_rate.sleep();
52  }
53 
54  // St all motor velocities to 0
55  send_cmd_motor_stop();
56  ros::shutdown();
57 }

87 void ArmUs::subControllerCallback(const sensor_msgs::Joy::ConstPtr &data)
88 {

91  m_controller.JoyLeft.set(data->axes[LEFT_JOY_VERT], data->axes[LEFT_JOY_HORI]);
92  m_controller.JoyRight.set(data->axes[RIGHT_JOY_VERT], data->axes[RIGHT_JOY_HORI]);
93  m_controller.Bumpers.set(data->buttons[LEFT_BUMP], data->buttons[RIGHT_BUMP]);
94  m_controller.Triggers.set(data->buttons[LEFT_TRIG], data->buttons[RIGHT_TRIG]);
95 
96  /*
97  m_controller.Pad.set(data->axes[PAD_VERT], data->axes[PAD_HORI]);
98  m_controller.Buttons.set(data->buttons[BUTTON_1], data->buttons[BUTTON_2], data->buttons[BUTTON_3], data->buttons[BUTTON_4]);
99  m_controller.Bumpers.set(data->buttons[LEFT_BUMP], data->buttons[RIGHT_BUMP]);
100  m_controller.Triggers.set(data->buttons[LEFT_TRIG], data->buttons[RIGHT_TRIG]);
101  m_controller.DisplayControllerInputs();
102  */
103 
104  // Switch modes (between cartesian and joint) with controller
105  if (data->buttons[BUTTON_3] == 1 && m_controller.Buttons.Button3 == 0)
106  {
107  if (m_arm_us_info->MoveMode == MovementMode::Cartesian)
108  {
109  m_arm_us_info->MoveMode = MovementMode::Joint;
110  ROS_INFO("Joint");
111  }
112  else
113  {
114  m_arm_us_info->MoveMode = MovementMode::Cartesian;
115  ROS_INFO("Cartesian");
116  }
117  }
118 
119  /********** Joint **********/
120  if (m_arm_us_info->MoveMode == MovementMode::Joint)
121  {
122  // Change joint controlled with controller
123  // Go up one joint
124  if (data->buttons[BUTTON_4] == 1 && m_controller.Buttons.Button4 == 0)
125  {
126  m_arm_us_info->JointControlled++;
127  if (m_arm_us_info->JointControlled > 5)
128  {
129  m_arm_us_info->JointControlled = 1;
130  }
131  ROS_INFO("Joint controlled : %d", m_arm_us_info->JointControlled);
132  }
133  // Go down one joint
134  if (data->buttons[BUTTON_2] == 1 && m_controller.Buttons.Button2 == 0)
135  {
136  m_arm_us_info->JointControlled--;
137  if (m_arm_us_info->JointControlled < 1)
138  {
139  m_arm_us_info->JointControlled = 5;
140  }
141  ROS_INFO("Joint controlled : %d", m_arm_us_info->JointControlled);
142  }
143 
144  // Get joint command from left joystick (set velocity)
145  m_arm_us_info->JointCommand = m_controller.JoyLeft.Vertical * MAX_VEL;
146 
147  }
148  /********** Cartesian **********/
149  else if (m_arm_us_info->MoveMode == MovementMode::Cartesian)
150  {
151  // Command is velocity of end effector wanted
152  m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.x = m_controller.JoyLeft.Vertical * MAX_VEL;
153  m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.y = -m_controller.JoyLeft.Horizontal * MAX_VEL;
154  m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.z = m_controller.JoyRight.Vertical * MAX_VEL;
155 
156  m_arm_us_info->MotorVelocities.m4 = (-m_controller.Bumpers.Left + m_controller.Bumpers.Right) * MAX_VEL;
157  m_arm_us_info->MotorVelocities.m5 = (-m_controller.Triggers.Left + m_controller.Triggers.Right) * MAX_VEL;
158 
159  // ROS_INFO("x = %f, y = %f, z = %f, a = %f, b = %f", m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.x,
160  // m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.y,
161  // m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand.z,
162  // m_arm_us_info->MotorVelocities.m4,
163  // m_arm_us_info->MotorVelocities.m5);
164  }
165 
166  m_controller.Buttons.set(data->buttons[BUTTON_1], data->buttons[BUTTON_2], data->buttons[BUTTON_3], data->buttons[BUTTON_4]);
167 }

310 bool ArmUs::call_inv_kin_calc_service(Vector3f &velocities, int &singularMatrix)
311 {
312  arm_us_msg::InverseKinematicCalc srv;
313 
314  // Send current angles of first 3 joints to service
315  Vector5f angles = m_arm_us_info->JointAngles;
316  // Send cartesian command to service (Desired velocities in x, y, z)
317  Vector3f commands = m_arm_us_info->CartesianCommand;
318 
319  srv.request.angles = { angles.m1, angles.m2, angles.m3 };
320  srv.request.commands = { commands.x, commands.y, commands.z };
321 
322  // If call to service is successful
323  if (m_client_inv_kin_calc.call(srv))
324  {
325  // Returns velocities of first 3 motors
326  velocities = { static_cast<float>(srv.response.velocities[0]),
327  static_cast<float>(srv.response.velocities[1]),
328  static_cast<float>(srv.response.velocities[2]) };
329  // Returns if matrix is singular
330  singularMatrix = srv.response.singularMatrix;
331  return true;
332  }
333  // If call is unsuccessful
334  else
335  {
336  velocities = { 0.f, 0.f, 0.f };
337  singularMatrix = 0;
338  return false;
339  }
340 }
